<div id="review_628613786" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/628613786" />
    <a title="Wendy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16831198-wendy"><img alt="Wendy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396967875p2/16831198.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/628613786?book_show_action=true">May 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Wendy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Wendy" href="/user/show/16831198-wendy">Wendy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Wendy by: </span>
      Author recommendation
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16831198-wendy?shelf=murder-mystery">murder-mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16831198-wendy?shelf=psychological-thriller">psychological-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16831198-wendy?shelf=crime">crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer628613786" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15867473712604879885">&quot;First Night Summer&quot; is an emotionally-charged psychological thriller set in Ruidoso, New Mexico, a quiet mountain town where Issac and Sarah Snow live with their twin daughters- Josie and Caroline. After the girls are publicly acclaimed for their heroic rescue of a four year old they are stalked by a psychotic pedophile whose sexual gratification comes from torturing, raping, and killing young girls. After the thwarted kidnapping of the twins and a tragic death, the family continues to be haunt</span>
  <span id="freeText15867473712604879885" style="display:none">"First Night Summer" is an emotionally-charged psychological thriller set in Ruidoso, New Mexico, a quiet mountain town where Issac and Sarah Snow live with their twin daughters- Josie and Caroline. After the girls are publicly acclaimed for their heroic rescue of a four year old they are stalked by a psychotic pedophile whose sexual gratification comes from torturing, raping, and killing young girls. After the thwarted kidnapping of the twins and a tragic death, the family continues to be haunted by a murderer whose lust for one of the twins is temporarily assuaged by his cross country abductions. Obsessed with tracking a killer who is targeting his family, Issac and his friend Ruidoso's police chief Charlie Biddle, find the task daunting;the only clues lie within cryptic letters with the words "do you like red" at the bottom.<br />Within the tapestry of a story that contrasts love and hate, unnatural obsession and humanity, forgiveness and retribution, are characters so realistic in their personalities and emotions that they leave an indelible impression on the reader; the former air force pilot Issac Snow, a man of principals whose strength and courage are tested, Charlie Biddle the police chief who must balance friendship with his dedication to duty, a loving wife and mother Sarah Snow's strength of character grows even when haunted by a tragic death. Juxtaposed against the evil mind of Ricky Doors the psychotic killer whose lust overshadows any humanity are his young victims, their minds shutting down, their innocence preserved in the face of their rapist's cruelty.<br />This is a true psychological thriller that tears at the reader's heart;a page turner that is as powerful in its intensity as it is thought provoking.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15867473712604879885" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


