  <span id="freeText17972674500037475295" style="display:none">This book is a matererly brilliant stroke of a creation it demanded a read in nearly one sitting. The story is creepy and gets under your skin. It enrages you from the sickness one can have and how it preys upon the innocent (Yes, I said "it" because the character is a Monster he has no right to be called a human anymore). This is my first read of this author and if his other works are like this one.....then I cannot wait to read them! This author knows how to character build and pull you into the story to the point you feel this is a true event (GOD I hope not). Even though the subject matter was disturbing, the author did have a way of approaching it without being too graphic. This is definitely one of the most thrilling, suspenseful, heart stopping books I have read so far this year!</span>
