<div id="review_939360262" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/939360262" />
    <a title="Nmkazzazyahoo.com" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10578157-nmkazzazyahoo-com"><img alt="Nmkazzazyahoo.com" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/939360262?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nmkazzazyahoo.com" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nmkazzazyahoo.com" href="/user/show/10578157-nmkazzazyahoo-com">Nmkazzazyahoo.com</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer939360262" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12081202591554742823"><br/>This book is a murder mystery. Unfortunately that is not very well described in the summary of the book, so some readers did not enjoy it. The book is very graphic<br/><br/>The book doesn&apos;t just cover the pedophile, the investigation, or the family&apos;s point of view. It is all covered and blended together nicely. The characters all have a good back story. Not so deep that it takes away from the main story but just enough to make you like them and understand them.<br/>After reading the reviews of others I was a l</span>
  <span id="freeText12081202591554742823" style="display:none"><br />This book is a murder mystery. Unfortunately that is not very well described in the summary of the book, so some readers did not enjoy it. The book is very graphic<br /><br />The book doesn't just cover the pedophile, the investigation, or the family's point of view. It is all covered and blended together nicely. The characters all have a good back story. Not so deep that it takes away from the main story but just enough to make you like them and understand them.<br />After reading the reviews of others I was a little apprehensive about reading it myself since I am a mother of four. However, I did not feel that the book was over the top. I think the point is to really open the eyes of some and to see how some of these predators set their traps. We can explain to our children how to "stay away from strangers" but most of these monsters know how children think. A child won't be "rude" to someone...they've been taught to have manners and that's where the lines blur.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12081202591554742823" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


