<div id="review_593849150" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/593849150" />
    <a title="Nancy Chaddick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17232788-nancy-chaddick"><img alt="Nancy Chaddick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599312516p2/17232788.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/593849150?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nancy Chaddick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nancy Chaddick" href="/user/show/17232788-nancy-chaddick">Nancy Chaddick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer593849150" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17046947875256818421">This is quite an exciting psychological thriller; made me stop what I was doing so as to get it read in a day! The tension created is almost more than one can bear but the ending makes it all worthwhile. If you are the kind of reader who refuses to flip to the back to catch the ending - you will love the excitement; don&apos;t give up if the first few chapters seem more than you can handle - there is a reward at the end. Reminds me of Odd Thomas books and others that just keep bringing the twists to </span>
  <span id="freeText17046947875256818421" style="display:none">This is quite an exciting psychological thriller; made me stop what I was doing so as to get it read in a day! The tension created is almost more than one can bear but the ending makes it all worthwhile. If you are the kind of reader who refuses to flip to the back to catch the ending - you will love the excitement; don't give up if the first few chapters seem more than you can handle - there is a reward at the end. Reminds me of Odd Thomas books and others that just keep bringing the twists to the tension. Highly recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17046947875256818421" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


