    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1058449071" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1058449071" />
    <a title="James Hannibal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26994766-james-hannibal"><img alt="James Hannibal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457376367p2/26994766.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1058449071?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Hannibal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Hannibal" href="/user/show/26994766-james-hannibal">James Hannibal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1058449071" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1975899042244526619">In First Night of Summer, Landon Parham takes on a difficult topic with dignity and extreme literary skill.<br/><br/>Every parentâ€”or at least every fatherâ€”should read this story. It is not a book to be read for entertainment&apos;s sake. It is a book that will raise your awareness of a terrible threat in our own backyard, encased in a story that will keep you on the edge of your seat and let you laugh and cry alongside characters that you come to embrace as family.<br/><br/>It is true that First Night of Summer is not f</span>
  <span id="freeText1975899042244526619" style="display:none">In First Night of Summer, Landon Parham takes on a difficult topic with dignity and extreme literary skill.<br /><br />Every parentâ€”or at least every fatherâ€”should read this story. It is not a book to be read for entertainment's sake. It is a book that will raise your awareness of a terrible threat in our own backyard, encased in a story that will keep you on the edge of your seat and let you laugh and cry alongside characters that you come to embrace as family.<br /><br />It is true that First Night of Summer is not for the faint of heart. Landon Parham hits his topic hard, with a high level realism that is certainly aided by his obvious skill as a writer. However, though the violence of the kidnapper's activities will make you cringe, there is a definite line that Parham does not cross. He DOES NOT describe the actual act of rape. He treats this subject of child abduction with dignity rather than gratuitousness.<br /><br />First Night of Summer certainly made me hold my own children closer. In addition to describing the ease with which a psychopath can grab a child, Parham also takes you deep into the villain's mind and history. He shows you how a sadistic pedophile is created, nurturing and growing the sickness at a young age while the parents are too busy and self-absorbed to notice. This book is a warning to take care of your kids because there are sickos out there, as well as a warning to guard against neglect that could allow other influences in this disturbed world of ours to prevail.<br /><br />First Night of Summer raises your awareness of child abduction to an acute level. I could attempt some reiteration here, but I could not hope to say it as well as the author already has. Instead, let me encourage you to read the book, and be sure to catch the Author's Note at the very front.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1975899042244526619" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


