    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_650883154" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/650883154" />
    <a title="Bookie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21645080-bookie"><img alt="Bookie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1372186087p2/21645080.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/650883154?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookie" href="/user/show/21645080-bookie">Bookie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780988802506" href="/book/show/17466894-first-night-of-summer">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21645080-bookie?shelf=ebook">ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21645080-bookie?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21645080-bookie?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer650883154" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16290167366860821446">VERY well-written and engrossing.<br/><br/>First Night of Summer is my literary surprise of the year. While there are many thrillers out there that lead the reader through a series of twists and turns, always keeping the stakes at life or death, there are few that can honestly captivate me from the inside out, touching places and chords seldom felt outside of my own tragedies or honest-to-God danger. First Night of Summer did exactly that. It affected me in places a book does not normally affect. It sang </span>
  <span id="freeText16290167366860821446" style="display:none">VERY well-written and engrossing.<br /><br />First Night of Summer is my literary surprise of the year. While there are many thrillers out there that lead the reader through a series of twists and turns, always keeping the stakes at life or death, there are few that can honestly captivate me from the inside out, touching places and chords seldom felt outside of my own tragedies or honest-to-God danger. First Night of Summer did exactly that. It affected me in places a book does not normally affect. It sang to me in voices tender and sweet. It broke my heart as the sea breaks against the rocks; violently and relentlessly, pummeling me to tears. To say that it is tragic...addictive...loathsome...uplifting...is to travel to the ends of the earth and say you journeyed far.<br /><br />I wish I could say more, but this amazing tale is difficult--at best--to fit into a box. Unlike any thriller or suspense I have experienced over my many decades of reading, this may be the one to finally shakeup the stagnant world of mass-production fiction. Indeed, it is bold. Absolutely thought provoking. And wonderfully simplistic at the same time. I await his next in utter anticipation.<br /><br />A word of caution. This magnificent novel is not for the faint of heart, nor the weak of stomach. But neither is the world we live in today. Read it and allow yourself to find the beauty within even the darkest of moments. My commendations to the author for deftly navigating a delicate plot. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16290167366860821446" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


